the black dwarf was a satirical radical journal of early 19th century britain. it was published by thomas jonathan wooler, starting in january 1817 as an eight-page newspaper, then later becoming a 32-page pamphlet. it was priced at 4d a week until the six acts brought in by the government in 1819 to suppress radical unrest forced a price increase to 6d. in 1819 it was selling in issues of roughly 12,000 to working people such as james wilson at a time when the reputable upper-middle class journal blackwood's magazine sold in issues of roughly 4,000 copies.